comments: Achiuwa (TOR) is raising his arm into a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs with DeRozan (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds without guarding an opponent when the shot is imminent.
Schroder (TOR) adjusts alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) places an arm against Siakam (TOR), who is off-balance during the rebound and releases without dislodging him from his position.
Siakam (TOR) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs as DeRozan (CHI) slips by for the layup attempt.
Schroder (TOR) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Siakam (TOR) releases the pass but continues moving forward and goes through White's (CHI) space, dislodging him from his defensive position.
LaVine (CHI) and Achiuwa (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal arm contact occurs between the two.
White (CHI) and Achiuwa (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal arm contact occurs between the two.
White (CHI) deflects the ball OOB.
Achiuwa (TOR) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with DeRozan (CHI), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) reaches to defend the pass and marginal contact occurs with Barnes' (TOR) right arm as he returns to the floor.
White (CHI) and Barnes (TOR) come together on the floor in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal body contact occurs between the two.
Schroder (TOR) is not legally established in DeRozan's (CHI) path when body contact occurs that affects his driving shot attempt.

A goaltend is called on Barnes (TOR) and the crew utilizes the goaltending/basket interference replay trigger. After communicating with the Replay Center, there is no goaltending on the play and TOR is awarded the ball for having possession at the time of the whistle.
Caruso (CHI) commits a take foul on Siakam (TOR).
DeRozan (CHI) gathers the ball and establishes his left foot as his pivot foot. He then slides his left foot prior to releasing the jump shot attempt.
Boucher (TOR) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward DeRozan (CHI) and initiates contact to his arm that affects DeRozan's upward shooting motion.

Siakam (TOR) and Caruso (CHI) come together during the throw-in and marginal contact occurs as Siakam releases away.  Caruso is not dislodged from his defensive position as a result of any illegal contact by Siakam.
DeRozan (CHI) steps over the plane of the free throw line before the ball touches the basket ring.
Barnes (TOR) closes out toward DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt and initiates more than marginal body contact after dislodging the ball.
Caruso (CHI) makes contact with the ball while simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Boucher's (TOR) right arm after securing the rebound.
LaVine (CHI) brings his arm toward Schroder's (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs during Schroder's drive.
Barnes (TOR) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Caruso (CHI) reaches toward the ball and marginal body contact occurs with Schroder (TOR) before he releases the pass.
DeRozan (CHI) initiates body contact with Boucher (TOR) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
White (CHI) makes contact with the ball while simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Schroder's (TOR) left arm as he releases the pass.
Caruso (CHI) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Siakam (TOR) prior to any incidental arm contact occurring during the drive.
Craig (CHI) is sliding toward Siakam (TOR) and marginal body contact occurs on the top of the perimeter.
